            "options": {
                "content": "About the difference between CPU and vCPU:\n- CPU: actual physical cores of the instances. Thread pool sizes are measured     in terms of the CPU. Instances may have different CPU limits due to different hardware.\n- vCPU: virtual cores of the instances scaled in order that all instances have     similar actual performance. CPU quotas correspond to vCPU.\n\nCurrently vCPU is not available in this dashboard.",
                "mode": "markdown"
            },
            "title": "",
            "type": "text"
        },
        {
            "datasource": null,
            "fieldConfig": {
                "defaults": {
                    "custom": {
                        "hideFrom": {
                            "legend": true
                        }
                    },
                    "unit": "short"
                },
                "overrides": [
                    {
                        "matcher": {
                            "id": "byFrameRefID",
                            "options": "A"
                        },
                        "properties": [
